Job description
If you are a Software Engineer with C/C++ development experience, please read on!

Located in Pittsburgh, we are a clean energy company that focuses on the idea of stationary storage systems that are high-performance, safe, sustainable, and cost-effective. We are an industry leader that is trying to fundamentally change the economics of power generation, transmission and distribution. 

What You Will Be Doing

The Software Engineer will join the systems engineering group and partner closely with the test engineering team. The Software Engineer will:

- Lead software and hardware integration projects to enable development and deployment of energy storage systems 
- Support integrated product testing and validation
- Write and compile source code for system controllers that interface from main controller to sub boards
- Design, test and procure chips, boards and simple controllers
- Set up remote telemetry and control of field installed system
- Provide primary engineering support for vendor evaluation, selection and qualification 

You will also play a key factor in finding cost reduction opportunities and will be responsible for technical and program reviews. 

What You Need for this Position

More Than 5 Years of experience and knowledge of:

- C/C++ Development
- Architecting relational database applications (SQL)
- Electrical Power Systems

We are looking for with their Bachelors or Masters of Science Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering or related discipline. 
So, if you are a Software Engineer with C/C++ development experience, please apply today! 

